clinical_study.brief_title: Evaluation of Carina Microphone Sensitivity and Maximum Stable Gain in Adult Recipients
clinical_study.official_title: A Prospective, Single-centre Evaluation of Carina Microphone Sensitivity and Maximum Stable Gain in Adult Recipients

brief_summary.textblock: This investigation is a single-centre, prospective, single-arm, post-market, non-interventional, pilot clinical investigation designed to characterize microphone sensitivity and maximum stable gain of the Cochlear Carina System.

detailed_description.textblock:
The totally implanted Carina System is an active middle ear implant where all components are implanted under the skin. Placing a microphone under the skin affects its acoustic sensitivity and vibration sensitivity. Software is now available to enable non-intrusive microphone measurements in existing patients with the Carina device, through a wireless link to the implant. Detailed knowledge of the acoustic sensitivity of the implanted microphone and objectively measured maximum stable gain, and its inter-individual variability, will allow more accurate calculation of overall system performance, and thereby more accurate prediction of clinical outcomes.
Subjects will attend one scheduled study visit to be assessed; several objective acoustic measurements will be performed that do not require active participation from the subject. No data monitoring committee will be used for this clinical investigation.

primary_outcome.measure: Acoustic Sensitivity of Implanted Carina Microphone
primary_outcome.time_frame: from date of enrolment through to study visit, an average of 1 month
primary_outcome.description: The acoustic sensitivity of the implanted microphone was measured using a white noise acoustic test signal was presented from a loudspeaker, with the sound pressure level monitored with an external probe microphone positioned over the location of the implanted microphone and the signal level at the implanted microphone recorded through a wireless link to the Carina implant.

primary_outcome.measure: Ratio of Response of Carina Microphone : Accelerometer for Acoustic Stimulation
primary_outcome.time_frame: from date of enrolment through to study visit, an average of 1 month
primary_outcome.description: Ratio [dB] of response of implanted microphone to response of implanted accelerometer, in-situ, for audiometric frequencies 250-6000 Hz, median and percentiles

primary_outcome.time_frame: from date of enrolment through to study visit, an average of 1 month
primary_outcome.description: Transfer function from Carina output to actuator [dB FS] to Carina input from implanted microphone [dB FS], for audiometric frequencies 250-6000 Hz, with ear canal open and ear canal plugged.

primary_outcome.measure: Carina Microphone Impulse Response for Acoustic and Actuator Stimulation
primary_outcome.time_frame: from date of enrolment through to study visit, an average of 1 month
primary_outcome.description: Identification of the system's acoustic and vibration transfer functions including non-linear components.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Eighteen years of age or older at the time of enrolment in the study
- Current recipient of a Cochlear Carina System.
Exclusion Criteria:
- Unwillingness or inability of the candidate to comply with all investigational requirements as determined by the Investigator.
